<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-22T14:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-22T14:36:00-05:00" n="1140" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1140">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4692</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-22T13:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 22, 1912—1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In the States of Morelos, Mexico, Puebla, Oaxaca, Michoacán and Guerrero
                            conditions are as bad as at any time during the two revolutions, if not
                            worse; disorders becoming more general; violence of the most barbarous
                            character daily occurring. The Government, apparently incompetent to
                            meet the situation, is losing what little prestige it gained from
                            victories in the north. I urge the most rigid precautions relative to
                            the State of Sonora where the Chihuahua barbarities will doubtless be
                            repeated in worse forms and on a larger scale.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>